The paper discusses the use of pre-trained contextualized representations for reading comprehension tasks in a multilingual setting, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as fine-tuning and pre-training, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves experimentation with different indexing and pre-training strategies, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
